&lt;h3&gt;Shabbat Parashat Yitro&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Shacharit Torah Reading&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exodus 18:1-20:23 (P 508, RP 471, WTC 409)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;7 Aliyot&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Shacharit Torah Reading Notes&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This week&#039;s portion contains the reading of the Decalogue (20:2-14). There are two sets of trope for this passage. The Ta&#039;amei Ha&#039;tachton are used for study and divide verses into a more manageable length. The Ta&#039;amei Ha&#039;elyon are used for public reading and give each commandment its own verse. We chant this section of the Torah portion according to the Ta&#039;amei Ha&#039;elyon. For the Ta&#039;amei Ha&#039;Elyon, see RP 476. For more information about the chanting of the Decalogue, and to see the two tropes set side by side, see ATC 78.&lt;/p&gt;
